==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: While
<hw>While</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hw⟦imac⟧l</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>hw⟦imac⟧l</ets>,
<ets>hw⟦imac⟧la</ets>, OFries. <ets>hw⟦imac⟧le</ets>, D.
<ets>wigl</ets>, G. <ets>weile</ets>, OHG. <ets>w⟦imac⟧la</ets>,
<ets>hw⟦imac⟧la</ets>, <ets>hw⟦imac⟧l</ets>, Icel. <ets>hv⟦imac⟧la</ets>
a bed, <ets>hv⟦imac⟧ld</ets> rest, Sw. <ets>hvila</ets>, Dan.
<ets>hvile</ets>, Goth. <ets>hweila</ets> a time, and probably to L.
<ets>quietus</ets> quiet, and perhaps to Gr. <?/ the proper time of
season. ⟦root⟧20. Cf. <er>Quiet</er>, <er>Whilom</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Space of time, or continued duration, esp. when short;
a time; <as>as, one <ex>while</ex> we thought him innocent</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧All this <xex>while</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This mighty queen may no <qex>while</qex> endure.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Some guest that] hath outside his welcome <qex>while</qex>,⟦br⟧
And tells the jest without the smile.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will go forth and breathe the air a <qex>while</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which requires time; labor; pains.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Satan . . . cast him how he might quite her <qex>while</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>At whiles</b></col>, <cd>at times; at intervals.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And so on us <qex>at whiles</qex> it falls, to claim⟦br⟧
Powers that we dread.</q> <rj><qau>J. H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <mcol><col><b>The while</b></col>, <col><b>The
whiles</b></col></mcol>, <cd>in or during the time that; meantime;
while.</cd> <au>Tennyson.</au> -- <col><b>Within a while</b></col>,
<cd>in a short time; soon.</cd> -- <col><b>Worth while</b></col>,
<cd>worth the time which it requires; worth the time and pains; hence,
worth the expense; as, it is not always <xex>worth while</xex> for a man
to prosecute for small debts.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>While</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: While
<hw>While</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Whiled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Whiling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cause to pass away pleasantly
or without irksomeness or disgust; to spend or pass; -- usually followed
by <xex>away</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lovely lady <qex>whiled</qex> the hours away.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>While</ent>⟦br⟧

