HEADWORD: While
<hw>While</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To loiter.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>While</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: While
<hw>While</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>During the time that;
as long as; whilst; at the same time that; <as>as, <ex>while</ex> I
write, you sleep</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>While</xex> I have time and
space.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Use your memory; you will sensibly experience a gradual
improvement, <qex>while</qex> you take care not to overload it.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, under which circumstances; in which case;
though; whereas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>While as</b></col>, <col><b>While
that</b></col></mcol>, <cd>during or at the time that.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>While</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: While
<hw>While</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>Until; till.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I may be conveyed into your chamber;⟦br⟧
I'll lie under your bed <qex>while</qex> midnight.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

